Huawei has gone through enormous hardships in the past two years, with the U.S. blacklisting it, blocking the sale of chips to the firm and the UK excluding it from its 5G networks. However, Huawei has risen in adversity by rolling out new products, creating its own ecosystem and persevering with R&D in 5G core technologies, as well as donating its openEuler system to the Open Atom Open Source Foundation, in an effort to build a stronger digital infrastructure at a faster speed. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Lily Lyu explains.